# DPUmesh bench registry — the hand-authored stand-in for the dpumesh-controller
# feed (NAMING.md §5). Baked into native bench images at /etc/dpumesh/registry
# (the resolver's default path); the preload validator writes its own at runtime
# because it needs the real ClusterIP for connect() resolution.
#
# Format: "ClusterIP:port  name  svc". Native bench peers are addressed by NAME
# only (resolve_name), so their IP:port is the placeholder 0.0.0.0:0 — no pod
# dials them by ClusterIP. svc = the interned service_id ([0,127]).
#
# ip:port          name              svc
0.0.0.0:0          bench-dpumesh     10
0.0.0.0:0          echo-dpumesh      11
0.0.0.0:0          loopback-dpumesh  12
0.0.0.0:0          echo-dpumesh-13   13
0.0.0.0:0          echo-dpumesh-14   14
0.0.0.0:0          preload-dpumesh   15
0.0.0.0:0          stream-dpumesh    16
0.0.0.0:0          verbs-dpumesh     17
